"],\"coloroption\":\"blue\",\"rowNumber\":\"row1\"}},\"26\":{\"type\":\"multipleBlocks\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockImage\":[\"76\"],\"myBlockHeading\":\"Youth Work\",\"myBlockTextboxText\":\"<p>Liz Dean Consultancy has teamed up with Laura Clark, a very experienced Sex Educator to advocate for the sex and relationship rights of people with learning disabilities<\\/p>\",\"myBlockUrl\":\"Communication\",\"tags\":[\"33\"],\"coloroption\":\"blue\",\"rowNumber\":\"row2\"}},\"28\":{\"type\":\"multipleBlocks\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockImage\":[\"62\"],\"myBlockHeading\":\"Relationships\",\"myBlockTextboxText\":\"<p><p>I have recently been working on behalf of the Brighton & Hove Healthy Schools Team and I have developed a teaching pack covering the impact and influence of the media and pornography on young people\'s sexualisation<\\/p>\",\"myBlockUrl\":\"Relationships\",\"tags\":[\"32\"],\"coloroption\":\"red\",\"rowNumber\":\"row2\"}}}}}', '2016-04-21 23:43:09', '2016-04-21 23:43:09', '17754fdb-d5ed-4d62-9521-3bef12a360e8'),
 ('36', '8', '5', '1', 'en_gb', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"PSHE\",\"slug\":\"pshe\",\"postDate\":1441133320,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"7\":{\"55\":{\"type\":\"singleBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockHeading\":\"PSHE\",\"myBlockImage\":[\"61\"],\"myBlockTextboxHeading\":\"PSHE\",\"myBlockTextboxText\":\"<p>I am experienced at delivering PSHE lessons on a range of topics, including mental health & well-being; sex & relationships; the impact and influence of pornography; the media & sexualisation; anti-bullying; stress management; nutrition; physical activity; sexuality\\/challenging homophobia as well as money management. I can deliver one off lessons, a series of lessons, organise a PSHE day \\u2018team\\u2019 delivery with a trusted team of colleagues or present at assemblies. Please contact me to discuss your requirements.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>I work to up to date good practice and guidance on PSHE delivery in association with (links to PSHE Association \\/ Sex Ed Forum etc)<\\/p>\",\"myBlockUrl\":\"\",\"tags\":\"\"}},\"64\":{\"type\":\"twoTextColumns\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockLeftColumnHeading\":\"Consultancy Work\",\"myBlockLeftColumn\":\"<p>Through my consultancy work I am available to plan, deliver and evaluate presentations,&nbsp;seminars, workshops or training courses (either half day or whole day) to practitioners, these include:<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul><li><strong class=\\\"redactor-inline-converted\\\"><\\/strong>The influence and impact of pornography and broader \\r\\nsexualisaion on young people\'s sexual health (including strategies and \\r\\npractical ways we can respond) <\\/li><li>Sex, Drugs & Alcohol : young people and risk taking<\\/li><li>Behaviour Change = theory into practice - specifically sexual health behaviour change or generic behaviour change<\\/li><li>Pleasure and sexual health promotion: taking a sex positive approach<\\/li><li>R U Ready?: Supporting young people to delay sexual activity until they are ready<\\/li><li>Sex, relationships and the entitlment of young people with learning disabilities <\\/li><li>Unveiling the mask:&nbsp;engaging&nbsp;young men in sex and relationships work<\\/li><li>Supporting young women in building resilience, confidence and assertiveness<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"myBlockRightColumnHeading\":\"Education\",\"myBlockRightColumn\":\"<p>I have a specific commitment and interest in ensuring the rights of <strong>young people with learning disabilities to adequate sexual health education <\\/strong>and can provide tailored training on this subject. &nbsp;This work is in conjunction with a very experienced colleague Laura Clark.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>See <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.lizdeanconsultancy.co.uk\\/?q=training\\\">here<\\/a> for more information on this work<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>The usual audiences for my courses are; Sexual health promoters \\/ educators, Teachers, GP\'s, Nurses, School nurses, Youth workers,&nbsp; Personal Advisers, Social workers, Health Visitors, Community & Voluntary sector workers and residential staff.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>I can also tailor and deliver any of the above topics to young people directly in or out of school settings. I hold a current full CRB check.<\\/p>\"}}},\"18\":\"\"}}', '2016-04-21 23:43:18', '2016-04-21 23:43:18', '11a320b1-c4ca-42f0-bd29-28b2a27dd85e'),
