 ('79', '2', '1', '1', 'en_gb', '22', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"WEBSITE CURRENTLY UNDER RECONSTRUCTION\",\"slug\":\"homepage\",\"postDate\":1435086771,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"24\":[\"62\"],\"7\":{\"82\":{\"type\":\"singleBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockHeading\":\".\",\"myBlockImage\":\"\",\"myBlockTextboxHeading\":\"Textbox Heading\",\"myBlockTextboxText\":\"<p>I am a self-employed practitioner in Health Promotion. My main area of interest is in Sexual Health and Relationships work however I have vast experience of working across a variety of areas, including youth work, education and social care covering a range of issues relating to health & well-being, specifically drugs, alcohol and mental health and well-being. I plan and deliver presentations, training courses, workshops and lessons. I also produce teaching resources and health promotion materials, conduct needs assessments and small scale pieces of research.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br>I am based in Sussex, but also work across the UK. I am passionate and committed to Health Promotion and sex and relationships work, specifically the entitlement of young people to high quality objective sex and relationships education. I have been working in the field of Health Promotion, Supporting Behaviour change, Motivational Interviewing and sex and relationships education for 15 years.&nbsp; I am a member of MINT (Motivational Interviewing Network of Trainers)<\\/p>\",\"myBlockUrl\":\"\",\"tags\":\"\"}},\"54\":{\"type\":\"twoTextColumns\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockLeftColumnHeading\":\"\",\"myBlockLeftColumn\":\"<p>As well as my extensive work with practitioners, I also work directly with young people, delivering lessons, workshops and 1-1 sessions. &nbsp;I currently work with The Young People\'s Centre in Brighton and the wider Youth Collective <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.brightonandhoveyouthcollective.org.uk\\\">www.brightonandh