 ('92', '2', '1', '1', 'en_gb', '26', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Home\",\"slug\":\"homepage\",\"postDate\":1435086771,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"24\":[\"62\"],\"7\":{\"82\":{\"type\":\"singleBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockHeading\":\"WEBSITE CURRENTLY UNDER RECONSTRUCTION\",\"myBlockImage\":\"\",\"myBlockTextboxText\":\"<p>I am a self-employed practitioner in Health Promotion. My main area of interest is in Sexual Health and Relationships work however I have vast experience of working across a variety of areas, including youth work, education and social care covering a range of issues relating to health & well-being, specifically drugs, alcohol and mental health and well-being. I plan and deliver presentations, training courses, workshops and lessons. I also produce teaching resources and health promotion materials, conduct needs assessments and small scale pieces of research.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br>I am based in Sussex, but also work across the UK. I am passionate and committed to Health Promotion and sex and relationships work, specifically the entitlement of young people to high quality objective sex and relationships education. I have been working in the field of Health Promotion, Supporting Behaviour change, Motivational Interviewing and sex and relationships education for 15 years.&nbsp; I am a member of MINT (Motivational Interviewing Network of Trainers)<\\/p>\",\"mainContentText\":\"\",\"myBlockUrl\":\"\",\"tags\":\"\"}},\"54\":{\"type\":\"twoTextColumns\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockLeftColumnHeading\":\"asdsd\",\"myBlockLeftColumn\":\"<p>As well as my extensive work with practitioners, I also work directly with young people, delivering lessons, workshops and 1-1 sessions. &nbsp;I currently work with The Young People\'s Centre in Brighton and the wider Youth Collective <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.brightonandhoveyouthcollective.org.uk\\\">www.brightonandhoveyouthcollective.org.uk<\\/a> &nbsp;This is important to me to ensure my training courses are kept in line with current practice (I also love this work :)<\\/p>\",\"myBlockRightColumnHeading\":\"sdasd\",\"myBlockRightColumn\":\"<p>My background is in the NHS, education and youth work.&nbsp; I have a BA (Hons)in Education and MA in Health Promotion.&nbsp; I currently work on a freelance basis developing and providing high quality training, developing educational resources and conducting needs assessments and small scale research. I also directly deliver lessons and workshops to young people in schools, colleges and youth settings.<\\/p>\"}},\"30\":{\"type\":\"singleBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockHeading\":\"\",\"myBlockImage\":\"\",\"myBlockTextboxText\":\"<p><br><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.fpa.org.uk\\/\\\"><\\/a><\\/p>\",\"mainContentText\":\"<p>I have been an Associate Trainer for the FPA for the past 6 years.&nbsp; I developed and deliver a one&nbsp; day course \'<em>Fantasy Vs Reality: the impact and influence of pornography on young people\'s sexual attitudes and behaviour<\\/em>\'.&nbsp; I have also co-written and deliver \'<em>T<\\/em><em>he Pleasure Principle<\\/em>\' and \'<em>Young people, sex and alcohol\'<\\/em>&nbsp;for the FPA. &nbsp;If you are interested in booking on these courses, visit&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.fpa.org.uk\\/\\\">www.fpa.org.uk\\/training<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"myBlockUrl\":\"\",\"tags\":[\"36\"]}},\"16\":{\"type\":\"multipleBlocks\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockImage\":[\"61\"],\"myBlockHeading\":\"PSHE\",\"myBlockTextboxText\":\"<p>I am experienced at delivering PSHE lessons on a range of topics, including mental health & well-being; sex & relationships.<\\/p>\",\"mainContentText\":\"\",\"myBlockUrl\":\"PSHE\",\"tags\":[\"35\"],\"coloroption\":\"red\",\"rowNumber\":\"row1\"}},\"23\":{\"type\":\"multipleBlocks\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockImage\":[\"60\"],\"myBlockHeading\":\"Health\",\"myBlockTextboxText\"