>Sex, Drugs & Alcohol : young people and risk taking<\\/li><li>Behaviour Change = theory into practice - specifically sexual health behaviour change or generic behaviour change<\\/li><li>Pleasure and sexual health promotion: taking a sex positive approach<\\/li><li>R U Ready?: Supporting young people to delay sexual activity until they are ready<\\/li><li>Sex, relationships and the entitlment of young people with learning disabilities<\\/li><li>Unveiling the mask:&nbsp;engaging&nbsp;young men in sex and relationships work<\\/li><li>Supporting young women in building resilience, confidence and assertiveness<\\/li><\\/the><\\/ul>\",\"leftColumnImageUrl\":\"\",\"rightColumnHeading\":\"Education\",\"rightColumnImage\":\"\",\"rightColumnTextboxText\":\"\",\"rightColumnText\":\"<p>I have a specific commitment and interest in ensuring the rights of&nbsp;<strong>young people with learning disabilities to adequate sexual health education&nbsp;<\\/strong>and can provide tailored training on this subject. &nbsp;This work is in conjunction with a very experienced colleague Laura Clark.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>See&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.lizdeanconsultancy.co.uk\\/?q=training\\\">here<\\/a>&nbsp;for more information on this work<\\/p><p>The usual audiences for my courses are; Sexual health promoters \\/ educators, Teachers, GP\'s, Nurses, School nurses, Youth workers,&nbsp; Personal Advisers, Social workers, Health Visitors, Community & Voluntary sector workers and residential staff.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>I can also tailor and deliver any of the above topics to young people directly in or out of school settings. I hold a current full CRB check.<\\/p>\",\"rightColumnImageUrl\":\"\",\"tags\":\"\"}},\"64\":{\"type\":\"twoTextColumns\",\"enabled\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"LeftColumnHeading\":\"Consultancy Work\",\"LeftColumnText\":\"<p>Through my consultancy work I am available to plan, deliver and evaluate presentations,&nbsp;seminars, workshops or training courses (either half day or whole 