 ('281', '8', '5', '1', 'en_gb', '14', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"PSHE\",\"slug\":\"pshe\",\"postDate\":1441133320,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"7\":{\"55\":{\"type\":\"singleBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"myBlockHeading\":\"PSHE\",\"myBlockImage\":\"\",\"myBlockUrl\":\"\",\"myBlockTextboxText\":\"<p><img src=\\\"\\/assets\\/images\\/globe280.png#asset:61\\\">I am experienced at delivering PSHE lessons on a range of topics, including mental health & well-being; sex & relationships; the impact and influence of pornography; the media & sexualisation; anti-bullying; stress management; nutrition; physical activity; sexuality\\/challenging homophobia as well as money management. I can deliver one off lessons, a series of lessons, organise a PSHE day \\u2018team\\u2019 delivery with a trusted team of colleagues or present at assemblies. Please contact me to discuss your requirements.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>I work to up to date good practice and guidance on PSHE delivery in association with (links to PSHE Association \\/ Sex Ed Forum etc)<\\/p>\",\"mainContentText\":\"\"}},\"122\":{\"type\":\"pairedBlock\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"leftColumnHeading\":\"Consultancy Work\",\"leftColumnImage\":\"\",\"leftColumnImageUrl\":\"\",\"leftColumnTextboxText\":\"\",\"leftColumnText\":\"<p>Through my consultancy work I am available to plan, deliver and evaluate presentations,&nbsp;seminars, workshops or training courses (either half day or whole day) to practitioners, these include:<\\/p>\\r\\n<ul><the influence=\\\"\\\" and=\\\"\\\" impact=\\\"\\\" of=\\\"\\\" pornography=\\\"\\\" broader=\\\"\\\" sexualisaion=\\\"\\\" on=\\\"\\\" young=\\\"\\\" people\'s=\\\"\\\" sexual=\\\"\\\" health=\\\"\\\" (including=\\\"\\\" strategies=\\\"\\\" practical=\\\"\\\" ways=\\\"\\\" we=\\\"\\\" can=\\\"\\\" respond)=\\\"\\\"><li>The influence and impact of pornography and broader sexualisaion on young people\'s sexual health (including strategies and practical ways we can respond)<\\/li><li>Sex, Drugs & Alcohol : young people and risk taking<\\/li><li>Behaviour Change = theory into practice - specifically sexual health behaviour change or generic behaviour change<\\/li><li>Pleasure and sexual health promotion: taking a sex positive approach<\\/li><li>R U Ready?: Supporting young people to delay sexual activity until they are ready<\\/li><li>Sex, relationships and the entitlment of young people with learning disabilities<\\/li><li>Unveiling the mask:&nbsp;engaging&nbsp;young men in sex and relationships work<\\/li><li>Supporting young women in building resilience, confidence and assertiveness<\\/li><\\/the><\\/ul>\",\"rightColumnHeading\":\"Education\",\"rightColumnImage\":\"\",\"rightColumnImageUrl\":\"\",\"rightColumnTextboxText\":\"\",\"rightColumnText\":\"<p>I have a specific commitment and interest in ensuring the rights of&nbsp;<strong>young people with learning disabilities to adequate sexual health education&nbsp;<\\/strong>and can provide tailored training on this subject. &nbsp;This work is in conjunction with a very experienced colleague Laura Clark.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>See&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.lizdeanconsultancy.co.uk\\/?q=training\\\">here<\\/a>&nbsp;for more information on this work.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The usual audiences for my courses are; Sexual health promoters \\/ educators, Teachers, GP\'s, Nurses, School nurses, Youth workers,&nbsp; Personal Advisers, Social workers, Health Visitors, Community & Voluntary sector workers and residential staff.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>I can also tailor and deliver any of the above topics to young people directly in or out of school settings. I hold a current full CRB check.<\\/p>\"}}}}}', '2017-01-04 00:57:59', '2017-01-04 00:57:59', 'd6aa40f1-334d-4f84-a892-04cd7b437109'),
