 ('7', '30', 'en_gb', '', '', '', NULL, '<p>I have been an Associate Trainer for the FPA for the past 6 years.&nbsp; I developed and deliver a one&nbsp; day course \'<em>Fantasy Vs Reality: the impact and influence of pornography on young people\'s sexual attitudes and behaviour</em>\'.&nbsp; I have also co-written and deliver \'<em>T</em><em>he Pleasure Principle</em>\' and \'<em>Young people, sex and alcohol\'</em>&nbsp;for the FPA. &nbsp;If you are interested in booking on these courses, visit&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.fpa.org.uk/\">www.fpa.org.uk/training</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More information:&nbsp;<a href=\"{asset:109:url}\">5833 Health Promotion Flyer April 2016 Final 308076</a><br></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2015-12-07 01:35:07', '2016-10-05 04:36:40', '318dbc6e-a0ff-499d-9f53-47266244c824'),
 ('20', '55', 'en_gb', '<p><img src=\"{asset:61:url}\">I am experienced at delivering PSHE lessons on a range of topics, including mental health & well-being; sex & relationships; the impact and influence of pornography; the media & sexualisation; anti-bullying; stress management; nutrition; physical activity; sexuality/challenging homophobia as well as money management. I can deliver one off lessons, a series of lessons, organise a PSHE day ‘team’ delivery with a trusted team of colleagues or present at assemblies. Please contact me to discuss your requirements.</p>\r\n<p>I work to up to date good practice and guidance on PSHE delivery in association with (links to PSHE Association / Sex Ed Forum etc)</p>', '', 'PSHE', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-24 19:04:52', '2017-01-04 00:57:59', 'd4232ede-1492-4111-9b2b-a79ee9e93e84'),
 ('21', '56', 'en_gb', '<p><img src=\"{asset:119:url}\">I am a self-employed educator, trainer, youth worker and facilitator. I have 15 years’ experience of working across a variety of areas and subjects including Public Health & Health Promotion; Behaviour Change; Motivational Interviewing; Youth work, Education and Social care covering a range of issues relating to health & well-being, specifically sexual health; drugs & alcohol and mental health and well-being. I plan and deliver presentations, training courses, workshops and lessons. I also produce teaching resources and health promotion materials, conduct needs assessments and small scale pieces of research. I am based in Sussex, but also work across the UK.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I am a member of MINT (Motivational Interviewing Network of Trainers) <a href=\"http://www.motivationalinterviewing.org\">www.motivationalinterviewing.o...</a><br><br>As well as my extensive work with practitioners, I also work directly with young people, delivering lessons, workshops and 1-1 sessions. I currently work with The Young People\'s Centre in Brighton and the wider Youth Collective <a href=\"http://www.brightonandhoveyouthcollective.org.uk\">www.brightonandhoveyouthcollec...</a> This is important to me to ensure my training courses are kept in line with current practice and the challenges and possibilities in this work.<br><br>My background is in the NHS, education and youth work. I have a BA (Hons) in Education and MA in Health Promotion. I currently work on a self-employed basis developing and providing high quality training, developing educational resources and conducting needs assessments and small scale research. I also directly deliver lessons and workshops to young people in schools, colleges and youth settings.I have been an Associate Trainer for the FPA for the past 8 years. I developed and deliver a one day course \'Fantasy Vs Reality: the impact and influence of pornography on young people\'s sexual attitudes and behaviour\'. I have also co-written and deliver \'The Pleasure Principle\' and \'Young people, sex and alcohol\' for the FPA. If you are interested in booking on these courses, visit <a href=\"http://www.fpa.org.uk/training\">www.fpa.org.uk/training<br></a></p>', '', 'About', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-24 19:23:30', '2016-10-25 19:33:58', '224250c6-c8ac-40be-8cab-b2e7d2565b57'),
 ('24', '59', 'en_gb', '<p><img src=\"{asset:76:url}\">Liz Dean Consultancy has teamed up with Laura Clark, a very experienced Sex Educator to advocate for the sex and relationship rights of people with learning disabilities.&nbsp;&nbsp; This is often a sensitive challenging area yet fundamental to ensuring positive health and well being.<br></p>\r\n<p>We can offer training to staff on the following areas in relation to learning disability; sex and the law; capacity and consent and translating policy into practice.&nbsp; We aim to build staff’s confidence and competence in addressing and responding to issues arising in a practical way – such as public vs. private behaviour; appropriate touching, developing and maintaining healthy personal relationships, sexualisation and issues relating to pornography, talking about personal relationships and sexuality (PRS) with your clients, contraception needs, STIs, sexual health, and sexual orientation.</p>\r\n<p>Our work in Sussex includes delivering training to staff at St Johns School and College; Barnados; Cherish Youth Club; YMCA; Extratime and the Community Learning Disability Team.&nbsp; We can offer bespoke training sessions to suit your requirements.&nbsp; We would build in consulting with staff beforehand to ascertain needs arising and current examples of practice relevant to training.</p>\r\n<p>We can also support the delivery of PRS education on the above issues in a style that is accessible to your residents using current evidence based high quality resources. Contact us for more information.</p>', '', 'Youth Work', NULL, '<p><strong>Pornography courses:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Visit the FPA for further details and information on how to book :&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.fpa.org.uk/\">www.fpa.org.uk</a></p>\r\n<p>I am happy to be contacted for more information on my work in the area of pornography and its impact. I often work with the media in supporting the research into television documentaries in this area. For example: http://www.bbc.co.uk/programme...</p>\r\n<p>These are some other examples of recent courses I have developed and delivered:</p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-02-25 01:23:00', '2016-11-02 06:19:52', 'ec67dd97-c60d-4fa4-bdc0-60042eb35675'),
 ('26', '65', 'en_gb', '<p><img src=\"{asset:60:url}\">I worked as a Senior Sexual Health Promotion Practitioner for the NHS in Brighton & Hove for 12 years. The main areas of my work were: workforce development for practitioners, delivering workshops and seminars, co-ordinating a condom promotion scheme and C-Card scheme, producing resources including a \'Risk workbook\' based on Motivational interviewing, leading on local sexual health media campaigns, chairing local partnership forums and supporting policy & strategy development in the field of teenage pregnancy and sexual health.</p>', '', 'Health Promotion', NULL, '', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2016-03-28 06:32:03', '2017-01-25 13:52:46', '6ecec5bb-4ac1-4380-bb93-56f942172d07'),
